By Lanre Adesanya
The Chairman of Lagos State National Union of Road Transport Workers (NURTW),Alhaji Tajudeen Agbede has lauded the concerted efforts of Governor Akinwunmi Ambode geared towards making the state attain its much professed mega status,affirming the development as one rightly timed commemorating Lagos at 50.
The NURTW boss also described the newly commissioned Jubillee Bridge at Abule-Egba axis of the state as a development that will have a multiplier effect on the economy of members.
ALSO SEE: Lagos history lecture now holds on May 24
Agbede made this disclosure while speaking with newsmen at his office in located along the area mentioned,he noted that the infrastructure will elongate the life span of vehicles plying it, stressing that Governor Akinwunmi Ambode is making great impact.
“Ambode your impact in the area of infrastructure is real,the newly commissioned flyover bridge will help to eliminate man hours usually wasted on this road,particularly in Abule-Egba here.
“For us transporters it will help bolster our income,as we will make more trips thereby making more money,it will also help to reduce earn the amount of monies spent on vehicle maintenance for this we are grateful”,Agbede reiterates.

			
